node.text: JC and Henok make time to catch up on their friendship that formed during the first Rate Beer fest and how Omnipollo's intriguing intersection of beer, pop culture and artistic exploration resonates so much with JC. Fast forward today and hear about how @omnipollo beer is available all over the world while at the same time setting down deeper roots in Sweden. We hit refresh on Covered In Puppies, our collaboration DIPA and its drinking beautifully. We miss you Henok & Karl!

node.text:
We'd like to extend a big thank you to everyone that supported this year's @c2cboston clothing drive. Together we nearly doubled last year's numbers, collecting almost 500 individual pieces of donated clothing, accessories, and toys for children in need!

@mrstrillium has done the honors of selecting our five lucky $100 Gift Card raffle winners. We will be reaching out to you shortly to coordinate your prize pickup.

node.text:
Blackberry, plum, and raspberry may seem like an unlikely fruit trio, but they came together to create one of our favorite Daily Servings to date. We knew we'd be revisiting this combination, ultimately pushing the fruit expression even further. 

Tomorrow, we'll kick off a week of fresh releases with Twice the Daily Serving: Blackberry, Plum, and Raspberry! Grab cans for Pickup in Canton, Fenway, and Fort Point, or order them shipped to your door anywhere in MA, DC, KY, NE, NH, PA, and VT.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Trillium Brewing Company on July 18, 2021 tagging @soakseltzer. May be an image of drink.

node.text:
Effervescent, vibrant in fruit flavor, lightly tart, and low in ABV, our lineup of @soakseltzer makes for incredible cocktail components.

Since their launch, we've been experimenting with different combinations, some simple and classic, others daring and novel. We'll be sharing them with you over the coming weeks.

First up: Cucumber Lime Gin Spritz! This one is all about effortless refreshment, combining your favorite dry gin with Lime Soak and a cool cucumber garnish.

Have you made any Soak cocktails at home? If so, we'd love to hear about them.

Featuring curly kale, radish, and turnip grown on our farm a mere 89 miles from the restaurant, we're excited to introduce a new salad to the Fort Point menu!

Topped with grilled nectarine, heirloom tomato, spiced sunflower seed, crema, and lemon vinaigrette, this summer offering is vibrant, crisp, and perfect for a hot day.

node.text:
Our UPS Direct selection is absolutely stunning right now and today, it's getting even better! Residents of MA, DC, KY, NE, NH, PA, and VT: upgrade your fridge or cellar situation in just a matter of days with our new stout additions from our online shop. Available to order at 9 AM:

Barrel-Aged Coconut Cake
Dusk Trill Dawn
Barrel-Aged German Chocolate Cake Doughnut
La Rien à Nuit

There is a limit of four bottles of each stout per person (16 total bottles max; 11 for PA). Shipping for 1-2 bottles will be $10/box and $20/box for 3-4 bottles. Cans will ship separately at our normal shipping rates.

Enjoy!

It's been far too long since we've seen this staple rolling down the canning line, but tomorrow, the double dry-hopped version of our flagship Fort Point returns for a rare Saturday release!

Hopped with Citra, Citra, and more Citra (for good measure), order cans for Pick Up and UPS Direct tomorrow morning. Don't sleep - it never sticks around for long.

node.text:
Trillium Canton's Mac & Cheese utilizes Orecchiette, handmade in-house daily with @groundupgrain flour, sourced locally from Hadley, MA. Creamy, aged gouda and cast iron cornbread crumbles round out the dish.

It's everything we look for in this staple. Velvety texture, just a touch of sweetness, and smile-inducing bite after bite!

node.text:
Coconut Cake is the dessert we crave when the weather is hot! The base version was originally released in 2019 and nearly two years later, the Barrel-Aged expression of this Imperial Stout is ready to be enjoyed.

Aged primarily in rum barrels, with a smaller percentage of bourbon barrel-aged components included, the resulting final blend is rich and decadent, yet deceivably drinkable.

Indulgent chocolatier aromas lead the way. Sweet, candied coconut, dense fudge, creamy vanilla, and rum-soaked oak staves make for a complex drinking experience, leaving the senses highly rewarded after each sip.

Bottles of Barrel-Aged Coconut Cake will hit our online store tomorrow at 9 AM for Curbside Pick Up in Canton, Fenway, and Fort Point. $26.05/500ml bottle, limit four bottles per person. Stay tuned for a special UPS Direct announcement coming soon.

Please note: This beer contains nuts.

node.text:
Nothing quite encapsulates the feeling of summer in New England like a raspberry lime rickey. We set out to replicate this classic, supremely refreshing beverage in a tart, pillowy, and sessionable beer form.

Cans will be ready to be enjoyed tomorrow when online ordering opens at 9 AM. $20.20/4-pack, limit one case per person.

Easing into the week with a moment of zen amongst the barrels.

There's a lot of care and attention that needs to be paid to these oak puncheons in order to ensure they have the positive impact on beer that we intend and strive for.

In these images, you'll see that we opt for steam (instead of harsh, damaging chemicals) to lessen the risk of microbial populations and to prevent any negative flavor or aromas. This is part of a vigorous quality program that ensures their overall integrity and useful life extends for decades to come.

node.text:
One of the larger Boston Harbor Islands, Peddocks is rich with history and home to Fort Andrews. It also offers a few camping sites, providing one of the more unique outdoor experiences in the region!

Its namesake beer is hopped with Citra and was the first in our Harbor Island Series. It's been quite a while since we've seen this beer, but we're certainly glad it's back - with some marked improvements.

Cans will be available tomorrow, kicking off a week that will offer plenty of variety, a special bottle release, and the long-awaiting return of a classic!
